abstract: President Donald Trump suggested on Tuesday that Democrats who don't want Bernie Sanders to win their party's presidential nomination tried to hurt the senator's chances by leaking information about Russian activities promoting his campaign. Trump gave no evidence for his claim.
snippet: President Donald Trump suggested on Tuesday that Democrats who don't want Bernie Sanders to win their party's presidential nomination tried to hurt the senator's chances by leaking information about Russian activities promoting his campaign. Trump...
lead_paragraph: NEW DELHI — President Donald Trump suggested on Tuesday that Democrats who don't want Bernie Sanders to win their party's presidential nomination tried to hurt the senator's chances by leaking information about Russian activities promoting his campaign. Trump gave no evidence for his claim.
headline_main: Trump Says Without Evidence Dems Leak Intel to Hurt Sanders
headline_print_headline: Trump Says Without Evidence Dems Leak Intel to Hurt Sanders

abstract: A frequent surrogate for Joseph R. Biden Jr. on the campaign trail, Ms. Owens has a résumé that reveals how politics, business and family converge for the Bidens.
snippet: A frequent surrogate for Joseph R. Biden Jr. on the campaign trail, Ms. Owens has a résumé that reveals how politics, business and family converge for the Bidens.
lead_paragraph: SWANSEA, S.C. — Valerie Biden Owens traveled past swamps, harvested fields and parked tractors to a small church, where she stepped off a bus to address voters. She had her talking points memorized.

abstract: The newly appointed U.S. official charged with overseeing disaster recovery in Puerto Rico said Tuesday that while the pace of federally funded projects to help hurricane and earthquake victims has quickened, he’s worried about long term efforts.
snippet: The newly appointed U.S. official charged with overseeing disaster recovery in Puerto Rico said Tuesday that while the pace of federally funded projects to help hurricane and earthquake victims has quickened, he’s worried about long term efforts.
lead_paragraph: SAN JUAN, Puerto Rico — The newly appointed U.S. official charged with overseeing disaster recovery in Puerto Rico said Tuesday that while the pace of federally funded projects to help hurricane and earthquake victims has quickened, he’s worried about long term efforts.
headline_main: US Official: Disaster Recovery Pace in Puerto Rico Sped Up
headline_print_headline: US Official: Disaster Recovery Pace in Puerto Rico Sped Up

abstract: A month before the Supreme Court takes up cases over his tax returns and financial records, President Donald Trump on Tuesday made the unusual suggestion that two liberal justices should not take part in those or any other cases involving him or his administration.
snippet: A month before the Supreme Court takes up cases over his tax returns and financial records, President Donald Trump on Tuesday made the unusual suggestion that two liberal justices should not take part in those or any other cases involving him or h...
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — A month before the Supreme Court takes up cases over his tax returns and financial records, President Donald Trump on Tuesday made the unusual suggestion that two liberal justices should not take part in those or any other cases involving him or his administration.
headline_main: Trump Says 2 Justices Should Sit Out Cases, but They Decide
headline_print_headline: Trump Says 2 Justices Should Sit Out Cases, but They Decide

abstract: Clusters of infection are likely in American communities, health officials said. Some lawmakers questioned whether the nation is prepared.
snippet: Clusters of infection are likely in American communities, health officials said. Some lawmakers questioned whether the nation is prepared.
lead_paragraph: Federal health officials starkly warned on Tuesday that the new coronavirus will almost certainly spread in the United States, and that hospitals, businesses and schools should begin making preparations.

abstract: Mexico posted its smallest current account deficit in 24 years during 2019 as sluggish investment crimped spending on capital goods even as the U.S. trade dispute with China supported exports, official data showed on Tuesday.
snippet: Mexico posted its smallest current account deficit in 24 years during 2019 as sluggish investment crimped spending on capital goods even as the U.S. trade dispute with China supported exports, official data showed on Tuesday.
lead_paragraph: MEXICO CITY — Mexico posted its smallest current account deficit in 24 years during 2019 as sluggish investment crimped spending on capital goods even as the U.S. trade dispute with China supported exports, official data showed on Tuesday.
headline_main: Weak Economy Fuels Smallest Mexican Current Account Deficit Since 1995
headline_print_headline: Weak Economy Fuels Smallest Mexican Current Account Deficit Since 1995

abstract: China is making U.S. lobster eligible for a tariff reduction, good news for lobster fishermen who lost a key export market during trade hostilities, Maine's congressional delegation announced Tuesday.
snippet: China is making U.S. lobster eligible for a tariff reduction, good news for lobster fishermen who lost a key export market during trade hostilities, Maine's congressional delegation announced Tuesday.
lead_paragraph: PORTLAND, Maine — China is making U.S. lobster eligible for a tariff reduction, good news for lobster fishermen who lost a key export market during trade hostilities, Maine's congressional delegation announced Tuesday.
headline_main: US Lobstermen May See Relief From Steep Chinese Tariffs
headline_print_headline: US Lobstermen May See Relief From Steep Chinese Tariffs

abstract: U.S. Senator Marco Rubio on Tuesday said he was confident the administration of President Donald Trump will extend a ban on oil and gas drilling off Florida, despite its enthusiasm for opening much of the country's coasts to petroleum development.

headline_main: Senator Rubio Confident Trump Administration Will Extend Florida Offshore Drilling Ban

abstract: U.S. Supreme Court justices on Tuesday signaled skepticism toward a federal law that made it a felony to encourage illegal immigrants to come or stay in the United States as they heard a bid by President Donald Trump's administration to revive the measure after it was struck down by a lower court.
snippet: U.S. Supreme Court justices on Tuesday signaled skepticism toward a federal law that made it a felony to encourage illegal immigrants to come or stay in the United States as they heard a bid by President Donald Trump's administration to revive the...
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — U.S. Supreme Court justices on Tuesday signaled skepticism toward a federal law that made it a felony to encourage illegal immigrants to come or stay in the United States as they heard a bid by President Donald Trump's administration to revive the measure after it was struck down by a lower court.
headline_main: U.S. Supreme Court Skeptical of Law Against Encouraging Illegal Immigration
headline_print_headline: U.S. Supreme Court Skeptical of Law Against Encouraging Illegal Immigration

abstract: The United States is preparing to impose more sanctions on Venezuela's oil sector, President Donald Trump said on Tuesday, in an attempt to choke financing to President Nicolas Maduro's government.
snippet: The United States is preparing to impose more sanctions on Venezuela's oil sector, President Donald Trump said on Tuesday, in an attempt to choke financing to President Nicolas Maduro's government.
lead_paragraph: NEW DELHI — The United States is preparing to impose more sanctions on Venezuela's oil sector, President Donald Trump said on Tuesday, in an attempt to choke financing to President Nicolas Maduro's government.
headline_main: Trump Warns of More U.S. Sanctions on Venezuelan Oil Sector
